We reject any kind of prejudged and the study includes a series of proposals for reforming the international financial architecture , such as they are present in the current academic and political debate , and it places this series of proposals in view of which we find ourselves .
While globalisation presents many other factors , including a social and ecological aspect , the report is central primarily to the international financial and monetary system and to the financing problems of development .
In order to draw up this report , we started by analysing the development of the globalisation process in the economic field and establishing a number of challenges linked to the financial and monetary system .
The report recognises the benefits of international economic integration , but it also noted the existence of systemic deficiencies and the persistence of an important problem : poverty reduction .
It confirms the need for official development aid to be more important and effective .
This report states that many countries have succeeded in raising their per capita income and improving their quality of life to a degree that they could not have achieved with a lesser integration strategy .
It also takes account of the high increase in foreign direct investment , which is fundamental to the strengthening of growth and , consequently , to the fight against poverty .
The report examines a number of existing proposals on international taxes .
With regard to the general use of these taxes as a potential source of financing for development or public goods , we have reached the conclusion that , although some of them seem attractive to the needs of both the short and the medium term , there is not much alternatives to financing from national budgetary resources .
This conclusion means readjustment of the priorities in the financial assets of the budget .
Another interesting proposal is the introduction of the tax on monetary transactions .
The report regards two perspectives : to begin with , as regards the so-called &apos; Tobin Tax &apos; or Tobin tax , in order to be a tool for stabilising currency markets , the analysis leads us to conclude that it is difficult to assume that this tax will essentially help to stabilise exchange rates .
However , if we look at this instrument as a tool for increasing the resources available for financing development , the Tobin tax can be more attractive .
It is certain that its application would prove laborious , because it should be covering almost all of the world in order to minimise tax evasion and it would require a strong international consensus .
Even in the event that such a consensus may be achieved at political level , there would still be many technical problems , including the problems linked to an appropriate tax basis and the recovery mechanisms .
These results coincide with the resolution on the international monetary system approved by the European Parliament last autumn .
Another important aspect of the report is the fact that commercial assistance and capacity development are important for a large number of developing countries if they want to be able to benefit from the growth opportunities resulting from trade .
